<P>A MEMENTO <HI>FOR</HI> HOLLAND: OR A True and Exact Hi&s;to<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="MURP" EXTENT="2 letters"> of the mo&s;t Villainous and B<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="MURP" EXTENT="2 letters">+barous Cruelties u&s;ed on the Eng<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="MURP" EXTENT="4 letters"> Merchants re&s;iding at <HI>Amboyna</HI> in the <HI>Ea&s;t-Indies,</HI> by the Netherland Governo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="MURP" EXTENT="1 letter"> and Councel there.</P>
<P>Wherein is &s;hewed What Tortures were u&s;ed t<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="MURP" EXTENT="1 letter"> make them confe&s;s a Con&s;pira<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="MURP" EXTENT="2 letters"> they were never guilty of; by putting them on the Rack, and by a Water torture to &s;uffocate them; and by burning them under their Arm-pits, and Soals of their Feet, till their fat by dropping extin|gui&s;hed the Candles.</P>
<P><HI>London,</HI> Printed by JAMES MOXON, 1<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="MURP" EXTENT="3 letters">.</P>
