<HEAD>The PRINTER TO THE READER.</HEAD>
<OPENER><SALUTE>Courteous Reader,</SALUTE></OPENER>
<P>_I Here pre&s;ent thee with a Story, which cannot be paralleld; that a Nation with whom we have had &s;o long confederacy; and for whom we have ventured our lives; and in who&s;e quarrel &s;o much <HI>Engli&s;h Blood</HI> hath been &s;pent, for the <HI>Defence</HI> and <HI>Regainment</HI> of their <HI>lo&s;t Liberties;</HI> without whom they could not have &s;ub&s;i&s;ted; by who&s;e Valour they have been maintained; and to whom they <HI>Owe</HI> their very Being; &s;hould thus be requited! for (only upon a <HI>pretended</HI> Con&s;piracy) to take away the lives (and that a <HI>Favour,</HI> their <HI>Tortures</HI> con&s;i|dered) of &s;o many innocent (eminent) men; meerly out of a <HI>Covetous De&s;ire</HI> to <HI>Ingro&s;s</HI> the whole <HI>Ea&s;t-India</HI> Trade to them&s;elves.</P>
<P>Let them pretend what they plea&s;e; God is
<PB REF="4"> a <HI>ju&s;t Revenging</HI> God: And although hitherto i<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="3 letters">h been pa&s;t by, and their execrable dete&s;ta|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">rranny (a name too good for &s;uch Rulers) <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="5 letters">h buried in the a&s;hes of Oblivion; yet (I <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 word"> the Generation alive are not &s;o degenerate, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 word"> will both Remember and Requite their <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="5 letters">ie.</P>
<P><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="2 letters">ey might have remembred th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">t if we had <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 word"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">&s;&s;i&s;ted them in th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">ir <HI>lowe&s;t Ebb</HI> again&s;t <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="4 letters">r pui&s;&s;ant Fee, One who (in his thoughts) <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 word"> &s;wallowed the Empire of Chri&s;tendome; <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 word"> would: Yet &s;ince the beginning of our <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 word"> happy Troubles, what Ayd have they &s;ent <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 word"> recover our Rights and Liberties? Surely <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 word">. Nay, have they not a&s;&s;i&s;ted tho&s;e who &s;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="2 letters">g<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">t to en&s;lave us?</P>
<P><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 word"> hope the Lord will put it into the hearts of t<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">o&s;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter"> <HI>Worthies</HI> &s;itting at the Helme, to take th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="2 letters"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="2 letters">&s;ine&s;s into their <HI>Serious Con&s;ideration.</HI> I l<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="2 letters">v<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter"> the i&s;&s;ue to God; having done my Duty as a <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">rue born Engli&s;hman, and a Lover of my Coun<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">ry; Farewel.</P>
